Since the range of working temperature depends greatly on the Curie temperature of MC materials, we will focus on near-room-temperature working MC materials for this review article [146–150]. Gd, or Gadolinium, is the representative material for a room-temperature MC material because it has a high magnetocaloric effect of 7.6 μB\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
